The sociodemographic characteristics of women were:
a) age group (18–29; 30–39; 40; 40–49; 50–59; ≥60);
b) self-declared skin color (white; non-white);
c) complete years of schooling (0–8; 9–11; ≥12);
d) family income in tertiles (1st: poorest; 2nd; 3rd: richest);
e) marital status (married; consensual union; single; divorced);
f) catholic (no or yes); evangelical (no or yes).

Regarding family and life experiences about violence, women were asked the following questions:
g) maternal aggression by intimate partner (yes; no);
h) sexual violence in childhood (yes; no).
